Replicaset
============
A replicaset is a kubernetes workload.
Purpose of replicaset is to mantain stable set of pods.

Deployment ----->manage------> Replicaset -------->manage--------> pods(set of pods)

1.Selector is used to identify the pods it wants to manage.
2.Replica count tells how many pods it can manage.

Replicaset use the pod templates rto create the pods.
Selector field helps replicaset to identify the pods it want's to manage.


A replicaset can also be a target of horizontal pod autoscaler.

apiVersion: autoscaling/v1
kind: HorizontalPodAutoscaler
metadata:
  name: frontend-scaler
spec:
  scaleTargetRef:
    apiVersion: apps/v1
    kind: ReplicaSet
    name: frontend
  minReplicas: 3
  maxReplicas: 10
  targetCPUUtilizationPercentage: 50

kubectl autoscale rs frontend --max=10 --min=3 --cpu=50%
kubectl apply -f https://k8s.io/examples/controllers/hpa-rs.yaml


 Set preferrence for which pod to delete first controller.kubernetes.io/pod-deletion-cost.
controller.kubernetes.io/pod-deletion-cost is an annotation in Kubernetes used to influence which Pod should be deleted first when scaling down a workload like a Kubernetes ReplicaSet or Kubernetes Deployment.
It lets you assign a priority (cost) to Pods, telling Kubernetes which Pods are more or less preferable to delete.
